'''Adam Feuerstein''' is an American journalist and columnist covering the biotechnology sector.
== Education == Adam Feuerstein completed a bachelor's degree in political science at [[Emory University]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://talkingbiznews.com/1/thestreets-feuerstein-leaving-for-stat/|title=TheStreet’s Feuerstein leaving for STAT|last=Roush|first=Chris|authorlink=Chris Roush|date=May 30, 2017|website=Talking Biz News|language=en-US|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-11-23}}</ref>
== Career == Feuerstein covered business, technology, and commercial real estate for the ''[[San Francisco Business Times]]'' and the ''[[Atlanta Business Chronicle]]'' as an assistant managing editor.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cision.com/us/2017/06/adam-feuerstein-preps-move-stat/|title=Adam Feuerstein Preps for Move to STAT|last=|first=|date=June 1, 2017|work=[[Cision]]|access-date=2018-11-23|language=en-US}}</ref> He later wrote about business software for Upside.com. In March 2001, he joined [[TheStreet.com]]. From 2005 to 2006 he worked as a research analyst for a hedge fund before returning to TheStreet. He resigned in May 2017. Feuerstein accepted a position as a national biotechnology columnist at [[Stat (website)|STAT]] in June 2017.<ref name=":0" />
Feuerstein is known for his style of reporting and his tweets to his large [[Twitter]] following.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.statnews.com/2016/05/02/adam-feuerstein-biotech/|title=Is Adam Feuerstein the most feared man in biotech?|last=Robbins|first=Rebecca|date=May 2, 2016|work=[[Stat (website)|STAT]]|access-date=2018-11-23|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/adam-feuerstein-follows-biotech-sector-151156225.html|title=How Adam Feuerstein Follows The Biotech Sector|last=Valleskey|first=Brianna|date=November 14, 2014|work=Benzinga|access-date=2018-11-23|language=en-US|via=Yahoo}}</ref> He often shares "unabashed" views on Biotech stock and the [[Food and Drug Administration]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PbHhgZd9VbEC|title=The Warren Buffetts Next Door: The World's Greatest Investors You've Never Heard Of and What You Can Learn From Them|last=Schifrin|first=Matthew|date=2010-10-01|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=|isbn=9780470915301|location=|pages=88|language=en}}</ref>
== Criticism == Feuerstein is sometimes the subject of criticism from different parties in the biotechnology sector.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/northwest-biotherapeutics-stock-woes-highlight-the-harm-of-short-sales/2014/09/26/78b99b0a-4507-11e4-b47c-f5889e061e5f_story.html|title=Northwest Biotherapeutics stock woes highlight the harm of short sales|last=Pearlstein|first=Steven|authorlink=Steven Pearlstein|date=September 27, 2014|website=[[Washington Post]]|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-11-23}}</ref>
