'''Maria Patrizia Grieco''' (born February 1, 1952) is an Italian [[corporate executive]]. She is currently the chairman of [[Enel]], the director of Anima Holding and [[CNH Industrial]], and a [[board member]] of [[Save the Children]].

==Life==
Graduated in Law at the [[University of Milan]], Grieco began her career in 1977 in Italtel, where she was appointed director of legal and general affairs in 1994, [[director-general]] in 1999 and managing director in 2002.

Over the years she has held various managerial roles in a number of large companies, including:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vita.it/it/article/2014/07/01/il-nuovo-presidente-di-enel-cuore-e-maria-patrizia-grieco/127392/|title=Il nuovo presidente di Enel Cuore è Maria Patrizia Grieco|date=2014|accessdate=February 10, 2015|website= Vita|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europaquotidiano.it/2014/04/14/chi-e-patrizia-grieco-nuovo-presidente-di-enel/|title=Chi è Patrizia Grieco, nuovo presidente di Enel|date=2014|accessdate=February 10, 2015|language=Italian|website=Europa Quotidiano}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2014-04-14/enel-patrizia-grieco-presidente-204619.shtml|title=Società partecipate dallo Stato, ecco i nuovi vertici|accessdate=February 10, 2015|website=I Sole 24 Ore|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lapresse.it/economia/scheda-nomine-chi-e-patrizia-grieco-presidente-enel-1.490687|title=SCHEDA Nomine, chi è Patrizia Grieco, presidente Enel|date=2014|accessdate=February 10, 2015|language=italian|website=LaPresse.it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=29981588&privcapId=7985050|title=Executive Profile Maria Patrizia Grieco|date= 2015|accessdate= February 10, 2015|website= Bloomberg}}</ref>

* managing director at Siemens Informatica (2003–2006)
* managing director at Value Team, today [[NTT DATA]] (2006)
* managing director at [[Olivetti]] (2008–2013), then chairman (2011–2014) 
* manager at [[Fiat Industrial]] (from 2012), today [[CNH Industrial]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://static.valored.it/_storage/documents/sala-stampa/temp_file_2013.09.23_Le30DonnePiuPotentiItalia1.pdf|title=Cassifica Le 30 donne più potenti in Italia|language=Italian|author=Maria Silvia Sacchi|date=September 23, 2013|accessdate=February 10, 2015|website=Corriere Economia }}</ref>
* director at Anima Holding (from 2014)
* board member of Assonime (from 2014)

Since 2010 she is board member of [[Save the Children]] and part of the honour committee of the Bellisario prize.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.donneoltre.com/donne_oltre/patrizia-grieco/|title=Patrizia Grieco|accessdate= February 10, 2015|language=Italian|website=Donne Oltre}}</ref>

In May 2014, Maria Patrizia Grieco became chairman of the board of [[Enel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/ca64d114-7a21-11e4-8958-00144feabdc0.html#axzz3R362jqhZ|title=Patrizia Grieco: agent for change in Italy|author=Rachel Sanderson|date=2014|accessdate=February 10, 2015|website=Financial Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euro2day.gr/ftcom_en/article-ft-en/1288660/patrizia-grieco-agent-for-change-in-italy.html|title=Patrizia Grieco: agent for change in Italy|date=2014|accessdate=February 10, 2015|website=Euro2day}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.corriere.it/economia/14_giugno_04/grieco-donne-vertici-quotate-cambio-passo-potere-13039d5c-ebd3-11e3-85b9-deaea8396e18.shtml|title=Grieco e le donne ai vertici delle quotate, il cambio di passo del potere|language=Italian|date=2014|author=Paola Pica|accessdate=February 10, 2015|website=Corriere.it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://valored.it/sala-stampa/le-donne-al-vertice-di-societa-quotate-cambio-di-passo|title=LE DONNE AL VERTICE DI SOCIETÀ QUOTATE: CAMBIO DI PASSO|author=Paola Pica|date=June 4, 2014|accessdate=February 10, 2015|language=Italian|website=Valore D}}</ref>

Since 2015 she is a member of the [[Trilateral Commission]].<ref>[http://www.trilaterale.it/Elenco_Soci_TC_Gruppo_Italiano.pdf THE TRILATERAL COMMISSION – Gruppo Italiano]</ref>

==Awards==

* In 2000 Maria Patrizia Grieco was awarded the Bellisario prize, a recognition for women who have distinguished themselves professionally, in management, science, or economics, nationally and internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lnx.fondazionebellisario.org/online/2000-2/|title=DONNA, COMUNICAZIONE E TECNOLOGIA|date=2000|accessdate=February 10, 2015|language=Italian|website=Fondazione Bellisario}}</ref>

