The '''World Communication Awards''' (WCA)<ref>{{cite web|title=World Communication Awards|url=http://www.terrapinn.com/2011/wca/|publisher=Terrapinn}}</ref> were established in 1999 to recognise excellence amongst global [[Telecommunication|telecom]] operators. The first awards were presented in Geneva during [https://www.itu.int/itunews/issue/1999/08/edit.html ITU Telecom '99] and were held at the Espace Sécheron<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://business.inquirer.net/238026/globe-telecoms-ernest-cu-ceo-year-finalist-world-communications-awards-2017|title=Globe Telecom’s Ernest Cu is “CEO of the Year” finalist in World Communications Awards 2017|access-date=2017-11-27|language=en}}</ref> More recent awards have been presented in [[London]] drawing an audience of around 500 senior executives from the [[telecommunications industry]].

Over the years, the World Communication Awards have evolved from being purely for telecom operators to encompass the broader telecom and ICT industry, with categories applicable to telecom operators and service providers, as well as vendors. In 2011 a sister event, the [[asiacommsawards.com|Asia Communication Awards]] was launched and is held annually in Singapore. 

The World Communication Awards are organised by [[Total Telecom]] and their owners Terrapinn. It celebrated its 10th year in 2008 with fifteen categories being presented, and with the chairman of the judges being [[David Molony]], former editor-in-chief of ''Total Telecom''<ref>[http://www.totaltele.com Total Telecom]</ref> and now an analyst at consultants Ovum.

Over the years the WCA have become more wide-ranging and international,<ref>{{cite news|last=Shaikh|first=Omar|title=Some of Your Favorites Voted World Communications Users’ Choice|url=http://www.techistan.com/2010/11/05/some-of-your-favorites-voted-world-communications-users-choice/|accessdate=11 January 2013|newspaper=Techistan|date=November 5, 2010}}</ref> with the 2007 winners including [[Bharti Airtel]], Minick, [[BT Group|BT]], [[NTT Communications Corp|NTT Comm]], [[SpinVox]], Afsat, [[Orange (telecommunications)|Orange]], ip.access, [[Botswana Telecommunications Corporation|Botswana Telecom]], [[TeliaSonera]], and Vivian Reding.

In 2016, Vodafone Carrier Services received the "Best Network transformation Initiative" award during the WCA, in London.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vodafone.com/business/carrier-services/vodafone-carrier-services-wins-best-network-transformation-initiative-world-communication-awards-2016|title=Vodafone Carrier Services wins Best Network Transformation award|website=www.vodafone.com|access-date=2017-11-27}}</ref> 

The 2017 edition of the WCA was marked by the nomination of Ernest Cu -President and CEO of [[Globe Telecom]]- as the "CEO of the year".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://business.inquirer.net/238026/globe-telecoms-ernest-cu-ceo-year-finalist-world-communications-awards-2017|title=Globe Telecom’s Ernest Cu is “CEO of the Year” finalist in World Communications Awards 2017|access-date=2017-11-27|language=en}}</ref>

